/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-ui-documentation_Result/260413_2033_Post_ENH_22/cache/doxygen_json/dali-ui/xml/classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AsyncImageLoader.xml:454:<para>The <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AsyncImageLoader" kindref="compound">AsyncImageLoader</ref> is used to load pixel data from a URL asynchronously. </para>
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-ui-documentation_Result/260413_2033_Post_ENH_22/cache/doxygen_json/dali-ui/xml/classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AsyncImageLoader.xml:458:<para>To keep track of the loading images, each load call is assigned an ID (which is returned by the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AsyncImageLoader_1a4d94e94fd7ec4dede82bc499a2c5afe7" kindref="member">Load()</ref> call). To know when the Load has completed, connect to the ImageLoadedSignal. This signal should be connected before Load is called (in case the signal is emitted immediately).</para>
/home/bshsqa/Shared/DALi_Doc_Generator/dali-ui-documentation_Result/260413_2033_Post_ENH_22/cache/doxygen_json/dali-ui/xml/classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AsyncImageLoader.xml:487:<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AsyncImageLoader_1ae231af6ae9edf94462538673ade6c089" kindref="member">AsyncImageLoader</ref><sp/>imageLoader<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1AsyncImageLoader_1a5804add5f3f038b7d2a33fd479d4540c" kindref="member">AsyncImageLoader::New</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
